    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix function signature mismatch in telnet command queue processing\n\n### Summary\nThe telnet server in OAI5G had a critical bug where functions with 3-parameter signatures were being cast to and called as if they had 4-parameter signatures. This occurred in the `telnet_pushcmd` function when `cmdfunc_t` functions were stored in fields expecting `qcmdfunc_t` functions.\n\nWhen these incorrectly cast functions were later called through the queue system with 4 parameters, it caused undefined behavior due to parameter stack misalignment. This led to incorrect signaling procedure sequences that violated the expected 3GPP message flow downstream of the `poll_telnetcmdq` function.\n\nThe fix implements a proper wrapper mechanism that ensures all queued command functions have the correct signatures when called.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv.c`: \n  * Added extended structure `telnetsrv_qmsg_ext_t` to store both queue message and original function pointer\n  * Implemented `cmdfunc_wrapper` to adapt `cmdfunc_t` signatures to `qcmdfunc_t` signatures\n  * Modified `telnet_pushcmd` to use extended structure and wrapper function\n  * Added `#include <stddef.h>` for `offsetof` macro\n"
}